reck.annotation
Class EntityImpl

java.lang.Object
  reck.annotation.EntityImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, Entity
public class EntityImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements Entity, java.lang.Cloneable, java.io.Serializable

A EntityImpl object acts as a Entity that contains type/subtype/class, a set of entity mentions/attributes corresponding to ACE 2004 definition.

Field Detail

ZEROMENTIONS

protected static final Mention[] ZEROMENTIONS
A leaf node should have a zero-length array for its children. For efficiency, subclasses can use this array as a return value for children() for leaf nodes if desired. Should this be public instead?

getMentionsAsList

public java.util.List<Mention> getMentionsAsList()
Returns a List of mentions for the current entity. If there are no mentions, then a (non-null) List<Mention> of size 0 will be returned. The list has new list structure but pointers to, not copies of the mentions. That is, the returned list is mutable, and simply adding to or deleting items from it is safe, but beware changing the contents of the mentions.

Specified by:
getMentionsAsList in interface Entity
Returns:
The mentions of the entity

setMentions

public void setMentions(Mention[] mentions)
Sets the children of this Entity. If given null, this method prints a warning and sets the Entity's mentions to the canonical zero-length Mention[] array.

Specified by:
setMentions in interface Entity
Parameters:
mentions - An array of mentions

setMentions

public void setMentions(java.util.List<Mention> mentionsList)
Set the mentions of this entity to the given list. This method is implemented in the Entity class by converting the List into an entity array and calling the array-based method. Subclasses which use a List-based representation of mentions should override this method. This implementation allows the case that the List is null: it yields an entity with no mentions (represented by a canonical zero-length Mention() array).

Specified by:
setMentions in interface Entity
Parameters:
mentionsList - A list of mentions to become mentions of the node. This method does not retain the List that you pass it (copying is done), but it will retain the individual mentions (they are not copied).
See Also:
setMentions(Mention[])
